            "answer_text": "Ethanol and hexanol have the -OH group in common. This is a highly polar group, which increases the solubility in water. The remainder of the molecules, CH3-CH2- and CH3-CH2-CH2-CH2-CH2-CH2- resp. are non polar: they will resist solubility in water (Like dissolves like!). The non polar \u201ctail\u201d in hexanol is much longer than in ethanol, and this makes hexanol insoluble in water. Solubilities of alcohols in water (in g/100 mL)methanol miscibleethanol miscible1-propanol miscible1-butanol 7,91-pentanol 2,31-hexanol 0,6 You see that the solubility decreases as the non-polar chain becomes longer. ",
