            "answer_text": "Ethanol is soluble in water because it has a hydroxyl group (containing an O-H bond) which allows it to form hydrogen bonds with the water molecules. Hexanol also has a hydroxyl group but as it is a long molecule, hexanol molecules have high dispersion forces (London dispersion force - Wikipedia) between them, making it harder to separate them. This is why hexanol is not soluble in water. Hope that helps! ",
